{"id": "duc04-testb-48:7#23", "contents": "The international community has condemned the arrests, with the White House and State Department expressing concern and calling for Xu's release. U.S. officials conveyed their concerns to the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Affairs and urged that Xu be released immediately. Xu's wife, He Xintong, said she does not know where he is being held and believes the authorities are unlikely to tell her. Xu, Qin, and Wang are all prominent figures in China's dissident community, with a history of activism dating back to the 1970s and 1989's Tiananmen Square democracy movement. Xu's wife maintained that her husband is innocent and that the authorities will have to \"expend a lot of effort to make him a criminal.\""}
